  sudo dmesg | grep -iE 'amdgpu|drm' | head -120
  ls /run/current-system/firmware/amdgpu/ 2>/dev/null | grep -iE
  'gc_|sdma|vcn|psp|mes|rlc' | head -40
  modinfo amdgpu | grep -iE '^(version|srcversion|filename|firmware)'

  7. Power-management state (a TTY-only crash that's stable under Wayland often 
